  "market_context": "Monday, 11 Sep 2023, post-New York open session. Price had formed an upward trend from 4222.00 to 4536.25, with a recent displacement up through down-close candles, establishing a bullish structure.",
  "key_observation": "A bullish breaker block (low-high-higher low) formed, and a fair value gap appeared at the breaker zone—creating a 'Unicorn' confluence—but price reached the projected target before the entry trigger (retest of the breaker/FVG) occurred.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified a 'high, low, higher high' sequence forming a bullish breaker block on the ES 5-minute chart after a displacement move through down-close candles.",
    "Step 2: Analyst marked the lowest down-close candle in the series as the breaker zone and noted a fair value gap present at that same level, creating a Unicorn setup (breaker + FVG confluence).",
    "Step 3: Analyst defined the stop just above the breaker and anticipated a retest of the Unicorn zone for a long entry.",
    "Step 4: Analyst observed that price instead moved directly to the target area (around 4536–4542) without retracing to the Unicorn zone, thus leaving the setup 'left behind'."
  ],
  "outcome": "No trade taken; setup was missed because price reached target before retesting the Unicorn zone.",
  "lessons": "Even high-probability confluences like Unicorn setups require price to actually revisit the zone. If the market moves directly to target without retesting the POI, the setup is invalid for entry—patience and strict adherence to trigger are essential.",
